image_analysis.description: A close-up photograph of a pair of heavy wooden double doors showing significant damage. The wood around the latch and lock area is splintered and gouged, suggesting a forced entry. The doors feature ornate brass hardware, including a long rectangular push plate on the left door and a matching plate on the right door with a 'Medeco' brand lock cylinder and a decorative, rope-patterned door knob. The wood has a dark, vertical grain.
image_analysis.layout: Vertical close-up shot centered on the door seam and hardware.

notes: The image appears to be forensic or investigative evidence documenting property damage, likely related to the January 6th Capitol investigation given the 'EFTA' (Evidence from the Archives) prefix often seen in such document sets.
